'''Beardslee Farm''' is a national [[Historic district (United States)|historic district]] and farmstead located at [[Pittsfield, New York|Pittsfield]] in [[Otsego County, New York]].  It encompasses five contributing buildings, one contributing site, and one contributing structure. It consists of the farmhouse, dependencies, and a small family cemetery.  The "L" shaped farmhouse is a large sprawling wood frame residence comprising three sections that reflects three separate building campaigns, ca. 1790, ca. 1800, and ca. 1810.  The main section is a two story, five bay building with a center entrance and a gable roof.  Also on the property is a horse barn, [[carriage house]], corn house, hop barn, and pump house.<ref name="nrhpinv_ny">{{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=7140|title=National Register of Historic Places Registration: Beardslee Farm|date=March 2000|accessdate=2010-01-14 |author=Kathleen LaFrank|publisher=[[New York State Office of Parks, Recreation and Historic Preservation]]}} ''See also:'' {{cite web|url=http://www.oprhp.state.ny.us/hpimaging/hp_view.asp?GroupView=7159|title=Accompanying eight photos}}</ref>

It was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]] in 2000.<ref name="nris"/>  

